       "body" : "It looks like the issue (https://github.com/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/issues/393) is with the Regex not selecting `$+{to_checksum}` and `$+{extra_numbers}` correctly. According to http://images.fedex.com/us/solutions/ppe/FedEx_Ground_Label_Layout_Specification.pdf\r\n```\r\nFor the FedEx Ground â€œ96â€ bar code, digits 2 through 8 are the\r\npackage ID number; digits 9 through 15 are the shipper ID. Digits 16\r\nthrough 22 are not used in the FedEx Ground â€œ96â€ check digit\r\ncalculation.\r\n```\r\nSo I've made the regex only select out 15 characters for the checksum, whereas it was `{15,20}` before. There's no test coverage for the 20 characters and I can't see any examples anywhere which would hit this.\r\n\r\n@jagtalon do you think this is suitable or have I missed something key? Unfortunately, not being US I can't test with my own package numbers!",
