       "body" : "Lo,\r\n\r\nA comment by @abeyang has reminded me about something I wanted to extend the dates role for.\r\n\r\nEssentially date formats that put the month at the front are uniquely North American; therefore I think it would be sensible to make the datesrole location-aware and prefer `05/20/2014` or `Jan, 01 2014` for US; but `20/05/2014` or `20th May 2014`. Especially for ambiguous formats (`02/05/2014`) this would be beneficial.\r\n\r\nSo, What do people think? Good idea, bad idea?",
