       "state" : "closed",
       "body" : "Default timezone was changed to make easier to discover instant answer. \r\n\r\nThe change has three parts:\r\n1) Trigger words was replaced with list of timezones. I think it makes more sense than trigger instant answer on each \"to\" or \"into\" preposition.\r\n2) Default time zone is user local time zone. \r\n3) Second part of the query was made optional. In current version it's necessary to implicitly type \"to <timezone>\", but it would be much more convenient to able to type \"19:30 EDT\" and have time converted to your local time zone. \r\n![screenshot from 2015-11-07 16 46 12](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1734524/11015872/2cda2674-856f-11e5-9b0f-5f717cade27b.png)\r\n",
