       "state" : "closed",
       "body" : "What does your Instant Answer do?\r\n\r\nReturns the country or purpose of a TLD (top-level domain). \r\n\r\nWhat problem does your Instant Answer solve (Why is it better than organic links)?\r\n\r\nIt allows you to see, at a glance, what TLDs exist and can be registered, and which can't. It allows you to see a short, straightforward answer with no clicks. \r\n\r\nWhat is the data source for your Instant Answer? (Provide a link if possible)\r\n\r\nNamecheap API: http://api.namecheap.com/xml.response\r\n\r\nWhy did you choose this data source?\r\n\r\nIt was the most reliable source I could find. \r\n\r\nAre there any other alternative (better) data sources?\r\n\r\nPossibly Wikipedia, but we'd have to update that static list whenever there's a new TLD. \r\n\r\nWhat are some example queries that trigger this Instant Answer?\r\n\r\n\".us tld\", \".in tld\", etc. \r\n\r\nWhich communities will this Instant Answer be especially useful for? (gamers, book lovers, etc)\r\n\r\nMost likely programmers or website devs. \r\n\r\nIs this Instant Answer connected to a DuckDuckHack Instant Answer idea?\r\n\r\nYep: https://duck.co/ideas/idea/1606/country-s-domain. This also carries on from another goodie implementation of this IA. \r\n\r\nWhich existing Instant Answers will this one supersede/overlap with?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\nAre you having any problems? Do you need our help with anything?\r\n\r\nI can't exactly get this to work (This is my first time creating a Spice from start to finish). \r\n\r\nWhat are the terms of use for the API? Will DuckDuckGo need specific authorization (e.g. an API key)? Are there any costs associated with API usage?\r\n\r\nNot really, there's already an API key in use with the Namecheap IA. \r\n\r\ncc @mintsoft ",
